                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_127-item1">
                     <author key="person_21990654"><supplied>Thomas of Chobham</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_4843">Summa confessorum</title>
                     <rubric>Liber de penitenciis</rubric>
                     <incipit>Cum miseraciones Domini sint super omnia opera eius</incipit>
                     <explicit>Et hec ad presens de penitencia dicta sufficient</explicit>
                     <note>Here with no author's name. Several leaves have been cut out and sewn in again.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 118)</locus>
                     <incipit>Penitencia igitur omnium criminalium peccatorum</incipit>
                     <note><bibl type="repertory">Bloomfield 3858</bibl>, this manuscript only.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 124v)</locus>
                     <note>Thirteen short sets of moral verses, a specimen of which is 'Si sapiens fore uis, sex serua que tibi mando | Quid dicis &amp; ubi, cur, de quo, quomodo, quando'.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On fol. 125v is added a late 14th cent. Latin passage about penitence.</note>
                  </msItem>
